 &HT;    In the Chiado, Cervejaria da Trindade, 20C Rua da Trindade,
(351-1) 342-3506, a popular beer hall in a former monastery,
specializes in beefsteak but also serves tasty grilled sole and
other fish. Dinner for two with beer or wine, about $22.
 &HT;    For Old World gilt, mirrors, crystal chandeliers and attentive
service, the place is Tavares, 37 Rua da Misericordia, (351-1)
342-1112. Closed Sunday afternoon and Saturday. Specialties include
stuffed crab and duck with prunes. Dinner for two with wine, $75.
 &HT;    Popular with the diplomatic community, Ja Sei!, 202 Avenida
Brasilia in Belem, (351-1) 301-5969, serves high-quality Portuguese
fare like roast lamb with thyme sauce, with a terrific view of the
Tagus. Dinner for two with wine, $60. Closed Saturdays and Sunday
evening.
