</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Take the cake!
 &HT;    (2nd sidebar for EASY-BAKE-OVEN03-COX)
 &HT;    Staff report
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Easy-Bake invites kids 8 to 11 to submit their favorite recipe
using one or more Easy-Bake brand mixes. Five finalists will be
chosen and sent to New York for the finals in October. Professional
chefs will help the finalists make their creations, which will be
judged by a panel of culinary and toy experts.
</P>
<P>
   The Easy-Bake `Baker of the Year' will win a $5,000 savings bond
and a two-year supply of bake sets. The four runners-up will win a
$1,000 savings bond and a year's supply of bake sets.
</P>
<P>
   Here's how to enter:
</P>
<P>
   _ Each entry must contain a parent or guardian's signature, the
name of the recipe, an ingredients list, mixing directions and
baking time on a 3-by-5 card, along with a photo of the finished
product.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mail entries to Easy-Bake `Baker of the Year' Contest, P.O.
Box 12462, Atlanta, GA 30355. Deadline is July 31.
</P>
<P>
   _ For more information, call (404) 681-8321. For a complete list
of rules, send a self-addressed stamped envelope to the address
above.
</P>
