<SLUG> BC-PETS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PUPPY LOVE 
</HEADLINE>
   Commentary  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By GLADYS ALAM SAROYAN  
 c.1998 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN PEDRO, Calif. _ I always wanted a pet. Once I even took home
a dog I found in a Beirut alley. But that was years ago, back in
Lebanon, and that stray dog wasn't allowed to enter the threshold
of my childhood home.
</P>
<P>
   I am now an American citizen who, along with dreaming in a
California accent, has become the owner of a purchased pet. He's a
little dog who, according to my Lebanese father, will fill my house
with all kinds of germs.
</P>
<P>
   You can't really blame my father the physician for his aversion
to animals in the home. He was the only person in Lebanon in charge
of infectious diseases. He could have lost his job if he blamed the
minister of health for Lebanon's unsanitary conditions. Instead, he
blamed the dogs.
</P>
<P>
   This puppy we call Dixie seems to like me. He follows me around
and chews the sandals I brought last year from my native country.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's like having a baby,'' my husband tells me. And I want to
believe him. I rub the puppy's back with the tip of my fingers and
he growls at me.
</P>
<P>
   When I sit on the couch, he snuggles beside me. I don't dare
move. I am afraid he will relieve himself on me.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kiss the puppy,'' my son says.
</P>
<P>
   I pucker up my lips. The dog stares at me. I bring my face
closer. He licks me. Oh my stars, quick bring me the heavy-duty
soap. I am certain I am now infected with an army of invisible
canine germs.
</P>
<P>
   But, when the house is empty, and it's just me and Dixie, there
is a feeling inside of me that surprises me. I think I am
developing a crush on this new addition to my family.
</P>
<P>
   I sure have come a long way from that little girl in Lebanon who
picked up a stray dog in an alley.
</P>
<P>
   Now, if only I can convince my father that Lebanon's woes had
nothing to do with the four-legged kind of dogs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-02-98 1230EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
