Clinton gives eight ``Mothers and Shakers of 1998'' awards to
working mothers who have found imaginative solutions to child care
problems. Winners include Sen. Patty Murray, D-Wash., and talk show
host Rosie O'Donnell. By EUN LEE KOH.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Sen. Robert F Kennedy, who was
murdered 30 years ago this week, is a major figure in the Kennedy
family Camelot legend. But death gave him an exaggerated glow he
did not have in life, as it did his assassinated brother, President
John F. Kennedy. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
