</P>
<P>
   A Broom Vac, for example, is worth $100, a Mop Vac gets $200,
and the Ultra Swivel Glide is worth $300 in Vacation Cash. Details
are in the product box. Dirt Devil is sold in stores nationwide.
For information, call 800-321-1134.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Turtle watch
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The largest sea turtle nesting site in the United States is
found along Florida's Space Coast _ Titusville, Cocoa Beach,
Melbourne, and Palm Bay _ and from now through August, visitors can
witness the nesting and hatching during moonlit guided tours
conducted by the Sea Turtle Preservation Society. More than 8,000
sea turtles are expected to lumber ashore to deposit eggs for
incubation. Of the hatchlings, only one in 10,000 is expected to
survive. For information, call 800-USA 1969.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   New Year's Eve
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Right now visitors to Paris wishing to see Versailles, the famed
chateau built by Louis XIV, will pay about $15 to tour the chateau,
but on this coming New Year's Eve, $1,300 will buy an evening to
remember. For the first time since the French Revolution, Americans
will be able to celebrate in grand style at Le Bal Du Roy in
Versailles.
</P>
<P>
   The evening includes a lavish dinner inspired by the original
royal cuisine from the 1700s; a fireworks display viewed from the
hall of mirrors, an 18th-century pleasure; music in the king's
chapel, and more. Participants this year will be given special
consideration for an even larger celebration on the turn of the
century. For information, write to Le Bal Du Roy, 35, rue La
Boetie, 75008 Paris, France; telephone 011-33-1-43-59-16-48 or fax,
011-33-1-43-59-16-49.
</P>
