<HEADLINE>
FETZER VINEYARDS CABERNET SAUVIGNON 1994 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Fetzer Vineyards Cabernet Sauvignon 1994 Barrel Select. North
Coast. About $13.
</P>
<P>
   For consistent quality at a reasonable price, year after year,
it's hard to beat Fetzer's Barrel Selected line of wines. This
rich, flavorful 1994 cabernet is an excellent example. The
appellation is North Coast because the grapes come from vineyards
in Sonoma, Napa and Mendocino counties. After fermentation, the new
wine remained in contact with the grape skins for two additional
weeks to gain extra color and richness. About 12 percent of the
blend is what the winery calls a special cabernet from Howell
Mountain in Napa County that was aged separately in American oak.
There's quite a bit of oak here, but then this is a fairly big wine
_ almost 14 percent alcohol _ and it handles the oak component
well. Everything is in balance.
</P>
</TEXT>
