<P>
   Did the man who uttered ``Oh, the humanity!'' at the Hindenberg
disaster get fired for his emotional outburst? And other stuff. By
ROGERS CADENHEAD. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TRULY-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The Fisk Rubber Co. used to employ an advertising logo
featuring a sleepy little boy, in one-piece pajamas, yawning,
holding a candle in one hand and with an old-fashioned automobile
tire over his shoulder. The copy with the illustration asked
simply, ``Time to Re-tire?'' Well, yes. It is. And I am. So this is
by way of a valedictory message. By PAT TRULY. Story has moved in
``k'' commentary category.  &QL;
