   SYMONS3 _ PALM BEACH GARDENS, Fla. _ Bishop J. Keith Symons has
resigned as head of the Catholic Church for the five-county Palm
Beach diocese. He says he molested minors early in his career.
Symons is the highest ranking U.S. clergyman to resign for
molesting children. (Moffett, Palm Beach Post). (Developing)
</P>
<P>
   w/REAX03 _ Local and national reaction about the Symons
situation. (Gushee, Palm Beach Post). (Developing)
</P>
<P>
   BOMB _ A 16-year-old male Little Miami High student is in Warren
County Juvenile Detention Center after allegedly bringing a bomb to
school. He's undergoing psychological testing and the crime lab is
testing the material. (Smith, Dayton Daily News).
</P>
<P>
   SHUTTLE _ HOUSTON _ While NASA officials hailed Discovery's
launch Tuesday as the end of an era _ the ninth and last space
shuttle docking with Russia's space station Mir _ it's also a
sobering warning that building the International Space Station is
likely to encounter unexpected problems and dangers. A last-minute
problem in Mir's motion control system threatened to delay the
launch, highlighting a history of problems that have plagued U.S.
And Russian space stations since the first ones were orbited in the
1970s. Includes references to astronauts Nancy Currie and John
Glenn. (Gaffney, Dayton Daily News). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDS: ETA is 8:45-9 p.m. EDT
</P>
