<TEXT>
<P>
   HORMEL-NOMINATION (Washington) _ The Clinton administration will
host a White House strategy session Thursday to devise ways to
pressure Republican leaders to allow a Senate vote on the
ambassadorial nomination of gay rights advocate James C. Hormel.
Some 60 people _ including leaders of civil rights groups, senior
administration officials and a bipartisan group of senators _ are
expected to attend the session and explore ways of getting Senate
action on Hormel's nomination to be ambassador to Luxembourg. By
JUDY HOLLAND.
