<P>
   CONRAIL-HEARINGS _ Two years ago, federal railroad regulators
approved, with hardly a blink, Union Pacific's acquisition of
Southern Pacific to form the nation's largest railroad. The result
was one of the nation's worst rail tie-ups, costing businesses
billions of dollars throughout the West. Wednesday and Thursday,
the Surface Transportation Board is holding hearings on plans by
two other railroads, Norfolk Southern and CSX, to take over
Conrail, the only major freight carrier serving the Northeast. By
Allen R. Myerson.
</P>
