two-decades-old biotechnology industry that is aimed at rheumatoid
arthritis, which afflicts 2.5 million Americans and is the most
severe of the diseases of the joints. What is more, other promising
new drugs for rheumatoid arthritis are right behind it, a stark
change for a disease for which there have been almost no new
therapies for years. By Andrew Pollack.
