<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
cli ents of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, June 3. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   LEIBOWITZ-COLUMN (Undated) - The courtroom filled up 20 minutes
before gavel time, starched collars all around, fine silk ties. The
players entered amid much hand-shaking and many hiyas. Everyone
knew everyone. The room buzzed with good cheer. You could sit
through a thousand court proceedings and never hear such a noise.
Tuesday was special, though , a reunion. The politicians and their
lawyers have been gathering at the state Supreme Court building
every few years, all decade long. The occasion: Fixing Arizona's
public schools. The result: Always more shame. By DAVID LEIBOWITZ.
Story will mov e in the ``K`` category.
