   &UR; WRITING GUTHRIE'S LYRICS INTO SONGS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; The British rock/folk-singer and composer  &UR; Billy Bragg &LR;  is
working on setting unpublished poems and lyrics by  &UR; Woody &LR; 
 &UR; Guthrie &LR;  into songs. An album called ``Mermaid Avenue,'' after the
Brooklyn street where Guthrie lived, will be released in June.
</P>
<P>
   Bragg started the project in 1992, says Musician magazine, after
meeting Guthrie's daughter in 1992. He says the lyrics deal with
unexpected subjects: ``My Flying Saucer,'' for example, and
``supersonic boogie.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S.  &UR; Joe Klein &LR; , the ``Anonymous'' author of ``Primary
Colors,'' changed publishers last week from Random House to Dell,
which announced plans to republish Klein's 1980 biography, ``Woody
Guthrie: A Life.''
