<TRAILER>
NYT-06-02-98 2159EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19980602.0417 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-02 21:59 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1173 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-RECRUIT-LADN     06-02 0315
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-RECRUIT-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC RECEIVER RECRUIT ARRESTED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Wide receiver Windrell Hayes, one of USC's top
football recruits, has been arrested in Lodi on burglary charges.
</P>
<P>
   Hayes, 21, was arrested May 22 with two other men on suspicion
of writing bad checks for merchandise, which they would then return
for cash.
</P>
<P>
   Also arrested were Derrick Small, 20, a student with Hayes at
San Joaquin Delta College and Curshawn McCurn, 18, from Lodi.
</P>
<P>
   Lodi police officers believe the trio wrote more than $15,000 in
bad checks. They purchased clothes, shoes and electronic
merchandise in at least six different cities, according to police.
</P>
<P>
   ``The detectives are still talking to a number of people and
number of victims,'' said Scott Fichtner, Lodi deputy district
attorney. ``Police reports are still being prepared.''
</P>
<P>
   A pretrial conference is scheduled for today, but with the
investigation ongoing, Fichtner said little is expected to be
accomplished.
</P>
<P>
   Hayes (6-foot, 200 pounds) is considered one of USC's impact
recruits. He started two years at San Jose State, leading the
Spartans in receiving both seasons. In 1996, Hayes was named
All-Western Athletic Conference second team, after catching 58
passes for 848 yards and four touchdowns. He is in San Jose State's
top 10 for career receptions with 97 catches for 1,383 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Hayes attended San Joaquin Delta in Stockton this year but did
not play football and has two years of eligibility remaining.
</P>
<P>
   USC coach Paul Hackett was out of the office Tuesday and could
not be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Hayes was expected to assume a significant early role for USC
because Hackett suspended star wide receiver R. Jay Soward from the
Trojans' season opener against Purdue for poor academic
performance.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
