replacements of both hips, both knees and the knuckles of her right
hand. But in the eight months since Ms. Lewandowski, 39, began
taking an experimental drug known as Enbrel, she is less fatigued
and no longer has to descend stairs backward to spare her knees.
``Life is fun now,'' she says. (Tim Shaffer/New York Times Photo)
