<P>
   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- June 2, 1998 -- GREEN-ZEBRA-TOMATOS, 6-2 --
Zebra tomatoes, a striking heirloom variety that can be tawny and
green or green on green, are now in specialty shops. These tomatoes
make delicious preserves and pickle nicely. In exotic recipes, like
Vietnamese chicken salad, thinly sliced strips of zebra pulp can
take the place of green papaya. (Jack Manning/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- June 2, 1998 -- FOOD-NOTES, 6-2 -- The
