<SLUG> BC-ADVERTISING-NOTES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMPAQ TO SHIFT A KEY ASSIGNMENT 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The Ammirati Puris Lintas unit of the Interpublic
Group of Companies in New York will soon lose a crucial assignment
from Compaq Computer Corp. _ primary responsibility for the
strategic and creative development of traditional advertising
campaigns worldwide _ to the DDB Needham Worldwide unit of Omnicom
Group in New York.
</P>
<P>
   Ammirati Puris and Compaq announced late Tuesday that they had
``mutually agreed to end'' their relationship on that assignment.
Ammirati Puris will continue to handle interactive advertising for
Compaq as well as direct marketing and media duties. The combined
billings on the account were estimated at more than $200 million;
it was not immediately clear how they would be divided between the
two agencies.
</P>
<P>
   The shift is effective when Compaq completes a deal to acquire
the Digital Equipment Corp., which could come later this month.
Ammirati Puris, which has worked for Compaq since 1991, has been
developing a brand campaign for several months. DDB Needham, the
Digital Equipment agency since 1994, jumped in with proposals for a
campaign that would promote the combined company.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is unusual, perhaps, for the incumbent to not be carrying
forward,'' said Andrew Salzman, vice president for advertising and
brand strategy at Compaq in Houston, ``but the DDB Needham creative
approach best represented the brand image and personality we
wanted.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-02-98 2249EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
